  <section>
    <title>Is Europe Disintegrating?</title>
    <subtitle>A Face-To-Face</subtitle>
      <chapter>
        <paragraph>
        <list type="unordered">
          <item>AUSTRIA: “In 2015, approximately 26,000 people crossed the Brenner pass
          to reach Austria and Germany. So, in order to avoid new refugees arrival,
          we’ve decided to close the Brenner pass.” The Fpoe (Austria's anti-migrant party) wins
          the first bailout with 36,7%.</item>
          <item>EUROPE: “The European Council condamnes Vienna’s decision because it goes against
          Schengen Agreement.”</item>
          <item>AUSTRIA: “Italy is not checking as well as it should migrants identity before
          crossing the border.”</item>
          <item>ITALY: “Migrant chacking is not only our responsability, also Germany and Austria
          should check You should also consider that Tyrol and South Tyrol have the same
          tradition, culture, language, that would be unfair.”</item>
          <item>GERMANY: “Brenner pass connects Italy to Berlin, and we already have a hugh number
          of migrants. If Italy doesn’t check properly migrants, we think that Vienna
          should close Brenner pass.”</item>
          <item>EUROPE: “Don’t you think about consequences? Other countries could feel legitimated
          by this event, doing the same thing in future Italy: Through the road crossing
          Austria, we exchanges €140b with other countries... Also our tourism, and South
          Tyrol’s tourism, would be demaged by this decision.”</item>
        </list>
        </paragraph>
      </chapter>
